List of top things to keep eye on when writing css

1) Livestyle guide
2) Story book
3) Avoid global and element selectors
4) Omit overly specific selectors
5) Use semantic class names ( BEM )
6) Don't tie css to closely to markup structure
7) Remove !important
8) Don't use inline styles
9) Don't use id for styling
10) Write inside out ( order of properties | 39% randomly | 45% Grouped by type | 2% By line length | 14% Alphabetical | https://css-tricks.com/poll-results-how-do-you-order-your-css-properties/ )
11) DRY
12) Grouping comments  
13) Use shorthand
14) 0px into 0

JOB NOTICES
1) id - Camelcase 
2) daDd, daChx, daIn
3) Order propertioes of elements ( normal, props, v-model, @events )
4) Use ` or ' or " in html ?
5) 

Components ( BEM )
.component-name { }
.component-name--modifier-name { }
.component-name__sub-object { }
.component-name__sub-object--modifier-name { }

Prefix
.l-layout        ( Layout rules )
.is-state-type   ( State rule )
.js-action-name  ( Non-styled Javascript Hooks )
.u-utility       ( utility | padding | margins | flex-box )




Resources
